Comments.Message:
A minor correction here. The method is called <pre> listWorksheetNames() </pre> and takes as input a parameter containing the path to the file whose worksheet names are to be gathered. If instead of using <pre> createReaderForFile($file_name) </pre> you wanted to detect the file type and then create a reader object based on the type of the file detected, the code would be something like: 
<pre>
$inputFileType = PHPExcel_IOFactory::identify($target_path);	// Identify the type of file.
$objReader = PHPExcel_IOFactory::createReader($inputFileType);	// Create a reader of the identified file type. 
// Get worksheet names in the file.
$worksheetNames = $objReader->listWorksheetNames($target_path);
// Print worksheet names.
print_r($worksheetNames);
</pre>
